oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Red clover for silage: management impacts on protein content in the season after sowing
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: O'Kiely, P.
Black, A.D.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Pasture and forage crops
Post harvest management and techniques
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Red clover cultivar (Merviot vs. Ruttinova) impacted on annual yield while an earlier harvesting schedule improved herbage digestibility. In contrast, the application of inorganic N to red clover in spring resulted in no benefit. This paper reports the treatment effects on crop crude protein concentration.
oai_dc:dc.dc:identifier: O'Kiely, P. and Black, A.D. (2007) Red clover for silage: management impacts on protein content in the season after sowing. In: Proceedings of the Agricultural Research Forum 2008, Teagasc, Tullamore, p. 111.
